<section class="container page join-page">
  <h1 class="page__title">Postdoctoral positions</h1>
  <p class="page__lede">We are hiring postdoctoral researchers to work at the intersection of mechanics, materials, computation, and design. If the group's work resonates with you, we would like to hear from you.</p>

  <div class="join-detail">
    <h2>What we look for</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Ph.D. in Aerospace, Mechanical or Civil Engineering, Applied Physics or Mathematics, Computer Science, or a related field.</li>
      <li>Expertise in some of the following: computational design, experimental mechanics, architected materials, origami and kirigami, additive manufacturing.</li>
      <li>Strong publication record and excellent written and oral communication.</li>
      <li>Ability to work independently, lead projects, and mentor students.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What we offer</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>A highly collaborative environment at the intersection of mechanics, materials, computation, and design.</li>
      <li>Access to state-of-the-art fabrication and testing (3D printing, imaging analysis, mechanical testing) and university HPC resources.</li>
      <li>Close collaboration across engineering, with opportunities to co-author high-impact publications and proposals.</li>
      <li>Competitive benefits per university guidelines, with strong mentoring and career development.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How to apply</h2>
    <p>Email <a href="mailto:{{ site.email }}">Dr. Chen</a> with: (1) a cover letter describing your research fit and goals, (2) a CV with publications and contact information for two to three references, and (3) a critical review of one of our group's publications. Review is rolling until positions are filled.</p>

    <p class="join-back"><a href="/join-us/">← All ways to join</a></p>
  </div>
</section>
